content: The team world championship is very close, it will begin after one week.
All the teams are doing the last preparations now,
Some weeks ago, we analysed the variant in d11 opening, from my game with Karlsson in Tampere Masters tournament.
Since d11 is so deeply analysed opening,
it is very difficult to invent something new here without taking big risks of losing.
In my game with Karlsson, I took the risk as white.
And in renjuclass lesson, some weeks ago, we reviewed this situation.
to neutralize the black power in upper area,
so that white could attack later in other areas without pressure.
However, there is a price on that attempt
The move 20-j13 was a good surprise tactics in short time limit tournament, thats for sure.
But before using such move in serious long-time tournament like team world championship,
it has to have a quality, not only surprise.
and black can go f8 without losing the game,
the the whole tactics of whites fails.
and then we ran out of time.
But later, we analysed it in our club here,
And we did not find white win here.
It is a very pity situation,
because if white does not win now,
then its already very difficult to balance the game
and the whole concept of 20th move may collapse.
Today we will begin our analysis from this point.
we will try to find white win,
and if not, then we can analyse if there are other playable variants for white from this 12th move.
tommy, attila89, xuwu, Ikon, yuelee00, dongfujia, Samsone, skywalker, smiling, slamduk, bendan, soujun, charles, Alex, shuwang, tianxia, SugarPuffs, jinzhiyuye, LOVE11, denise, StarRain, Erica.

sometimes we find good moves, sometimes not
Here, it seems black has to defend at f7 sooner or later.
if black still have the tempo that's not problem,to take f7,is it?
however, your 17th move can be a good surprise tactics in short time tournaments
maybe white should consider using f7

no matter what, i am glad to see such creative ideas, such as the h12

Even if theoretically white can do better here,
not everybody can find best moves in real game,
so the 17th move can be a very good surprise
the optimal theory of this 12th move will concentrate on this variant here.
These 16 moves may be strongest for both sides.
I believe the team world championship will give some interesting games in this variant.

and black will try to defend in the way which keeps black power alive.
